#   URI tickets: branch/commit naming

Tickets that unify Beagle's branch-vs-commit-hash disambiguation behind one keeper-owned, branch-first, hash-length-agnostic rule (origin in [DIS-025], grammar in [URI-spec]). Each entry below is one ticket with its live state; an entry drops off once the whole ticket closes. The fix-and-land method is [Issues].

##  Active tickets

 -  [URI-001] — unify branch/commit naming; St.1 branch-first + St.2 length-agnostic full-sha + St.3 scope-only canonical form landed; St.4-5 (retire guessers, remote delegation) pending.
 -  [URI-002] — unify bang-factor handling across all verbs/dogs: a per-component bang bitflag byte (verb/path/query/fragment) + one `dog/` debanger that strips a `!` (shift slice by one) and sets the bit, replacing the ad-hoc `dog/CLI.c` verb-bang→`--force` shim.

